HEADWORD: Provection
<hw>Pro*vec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>provectio</ets> an advancement.]</ety> <fld>(Philol.)</fld> <def>A
carrying forward, as of a final letter, to a following word; <as>as, for
example, a <ex>nickname</ex> for <ex>an ekename</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

